title.narrative: Ministry of Health has improved capacity to generate quality information (disaggregated by age and sex) and use evidence for programme improvement.

description.narrative: To enhance generation and utilization of data to inform evidence programming, perinatal and neonatal death notification increased from 16 per cent in 2018 to 46 per cent in 2019 and perinatal and neonatal death surveillance was conducted in 100% government and private maternity health facilities. Client Satisfaction Feedback Mechanism was established through integration of RapidPro and Client Information Management Systems (CMIS), which will enhance evidence-based quality improvement in all the health facilities with CMIS. To enhance health sector evidence generation, four programme annual reports with age and gender disaggregated data were produced. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:18/12/2019
